section.Text:
When you have @scania/theme-light installed, you can use the available tokens with css variable. You only need to add 'sdds-' prefix before the token name.

```
// style.css

.my-div {
    padding: var(--sdds-spacing-layout-32);
}

.my-box {
    padding: var(--sdds-spacing-element-4);
}

```

To use SCSS variable, you need to install grid package.

```
npm i @scania/grid --save-dev
```

After you install the package, you can import the scss into your application.

```
@import '~node_modules/@scania/grid/dist/scss/grid';
```

Now you can start using the SCSS variables for the design tokens.

```
.my-class {
    padding: $spacing-element-16;
}

@media (min-width: $screen-md) {
    margin: $spacing-layout-32;
 }
```

